The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 06 December is 9,583 (1,109.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 01 December, there were 484 new confirmed cases (56.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 24 November, there were 608 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 20% (124 fewer cases).
